   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">\n",
    "    Displaying LLM Outputs\n",
    "</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">\n",
    "    The Copy Paste\n",
    "</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "![Writing Emails at University](email.png){fig-cap=\"A university student writing an email to a professor\" width=70%}\n",
    "\n",
    "Here’s a short example of ChatGPT writing an email\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### **The Email Draft**\n",
    "\n",
    "This week I had to email a professor about missing class for a family commitment. Normally, I would just write it myself, but I wanted to see how ChatGPT would handle the situation. I asked:\n",
    "\n",
    "**“Write me a polite email to my professor explaining I will miss class on Friday due to a family event.”**\n",
    "\n",
    "The model produced the following draft:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Subject:** Request to Miss Class on Friday  \n",
    "> Dear Professor,  \n",
    "> I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to let you know that I will not be able to attend class on Friday due to a family event. I will make sure to catch up on the material covered. Thank you for your understanding.  \n",
    "> Sincerely, [Your Name]\n",
    "\n",
    "I thought this was actually pretty close to what I’d send. The tone was respectful and professional, but it was also a little too generic. I edited it to include the course name and asked if there was anything I should review before the next class.  \n",
    "\n",
    "This showed me that while ChatGPT is a good starting point, I still need to personalize the response to sound like *me*.  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">\n",
    "    Some alternatives\n",
    "</h1>\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">\n",
    "    The Quote\n",
    "</h4>\n",
    "> Write me a polite email to my professor about missing class\n",
    "Of course! Would you like me to keep it formal, or more casual?\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">\n",
    "    Changing Background Colors\n",
    "</h4>\n",
    "<p style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "    Of course! Would you like me to keep it formal, or more casual?\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">\n",
    "    Combination of both!\n",
    "</h4>\n",
    "**Prompt**\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "    <blockquote>\n",
    "        Write me a polite email to my professor about missing class\n",
    "    </blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "**Response**\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "    <blockquote>\n",
    "        Of course! Would you like me to keep it formal, or more casual?\n",
    "    </blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">\n",
    "    Integrating responses\n",
    "</h1>\n",
    "This week I wanted to explore how GPT-5 handles **student communication tasks**. We often hear about people using it for essays or coding, but I think everyday uses like emailing professors are just as important.  \n",
    "\n",
    "When I tested it, the response was professional and grammatically correct, but also generic. In practice, I’d use it as a **template**, then tweak details to make sure it sounds like me.  \n",
    "\n",
    "This made me think about how LLMs shape communication: they’re great at giving us a baseline of clarity and politeness, but personalization still matters — especially in academic settings where tone can affect relationships.\n"
   ]
